      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINH TEDDY (1) got the job done again after running them ragged to make it two on the bounce, scoring by 0.8 lengths (24.74) at Sale over 435m. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from six starts. In form and can go on with it. DR. HOPPER (6) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 3.5 lengths (24.20) at Traralgon. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MIA NEO (5) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Healesville over 350m behind Daring Bandit (19.72) in a Grade 5. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Better than last start and can bounce back. DESPICABLE ANDY (7) is a last start winner in very good time. Right in the mix.",
